===Etymology===
From the German ''[[Rotogravur]]'', derived from the Berlin printing firm [[w:Rotogravur Deutsche Tiefdruck Gesellschaft|Rotogravur Deutsche Tiefdruck Gesellschaft]], the name of which is conjectured to be a portmanteau of [[w:Rotophot|Rotophot]] and [[w:Deutshe Photogravur|Deutshe Photogravur]].

===Noun===
'''rotogravure'''
# A [[printing]] process by which the paper is rolled through [[intaglio]] [[cylinder]]s.
# A [[print]] made by such a method.
# The [[portion]] of a printed work produced by this method.

